      • registerPrototypeModel

        public static void registerPrototypeModel(Processor prototypeModel)
        Register a prototype model against its identifier (ie. processor.getModelIdentifier() ).

        When asked to load a model with the same model identifier, the supplied prototype will be cloned and returned.

        Parameters:
        prototypeModel - the prototype model to register.

      • loadProcessor

        public static Processor loadProcessor(Element xmlNode,
                      boolean useExistingIfPossible)
        Loads a processor from the given XML Element, optionally using an already-loaded Processor (otherwise a clone is created).
        Parameters:
        xmlNode - the XML Element from which to load the Processor.
        useExistingIfPossible - if true, will return an already-existing Processor with the same UUID. Otherwise a new version is created.
        Returns:
        the loaded Processor.
